Subject: SQL job stopped running and won't start
Description: We have an important production custom job that pulls login activity every few minutes across the environment. It has stopped running and will not start. We have traced and it seems to be missing a hostlist record. We have reviewed the host list adn it look good and all other jobs are running via the same host list. here is the call SELECT HM.Name,HM.FQDN,HM.hostID FROM SA_HostMasterTbl AS HM WHERE HM.hostID in (Select HostListsContentTbl.hostID from HostListsContentTbl where HostListsContentTbl.listID='{5D376271-0FAC-4B6B-A43A-9B26AAC0DC9D}')
Solution_Comment__c:
customer has reworked their login collection.
Now jobs run as expected.
